stone","text":"Go reference: pkg/analysis/advanced.go — Four advanced analysis types: (1) TopKSet: nodes appearing in top-K across multiple metrics simultaneously (the 'keystone' issues). (2) CoverageSet: greedy minimum set that touches all clusters (for maximum impact work). (3) KPaths: k-shortest paths between specified nodes using Yen's algorithm. (4) CycleBreak: minimum feedback arc set to break all cycles (NP-hard, use greedy approximation). All four use petgraph algorithms.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:06:45Z"},{"id":54,"issue_id":"bd-ybj.5","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"CORRECTION: Previous description listed only 4 advanced insight types but Go has 6. The full AdvancedInsights struct from advanced_insights.go lines 58-84 contains: TopKSet (submodular selection for max unlock), CoverageSet (greedy vertex cover), KPaths (k-shortest critical paths), CycleBreak (minimum feedback arc set), PLUS two additional types: ParallelCut (parallel cut analysis) and ParallelGain (parallel gain analysis). The Rust implementation must include all 6 types. The AdvancedInsightsConfig and UsageHints fields must also be included.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:33:14Z"},{"id":75,"issue_id":"bd-ybj.5","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"TESTING REQUIREMENT: This task is NOT complete until it includes inline unit tests with deterministic graph fixtures. Tests must cover: (1) happy path with known expected values, (2) empty graph edge case, (3) single-node graph, (4) large graph (100+ nodes) for correctness. Use assert!((actual - expected).abs() < 1e-6) for float comparisons.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:37:16Z"}]}
